# Naming Conventions

## General

- Use clear, readable names — avoid abbreviations and technical jargon
- Variables and functions: `camelCase` with descriptive intent
- Types and interfaces: `PascalCase`
- Config constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` (e.g. `TARGET_AT_40`, `BIRTH_YEAR`, `PROJECTION_YEARS`)

## Files

| Folder | Pattern | Example |
|--------|---------|---------|
| config | `{name}.config.ts` | `investment.config.ts` |
| utils | `{name}.util.ts` | `investmentCalculation.util.ts` |
| hooks | `{domain}.hooks.ts` | `investment.hooks.ts` |
| contexts | `{Name}Context.tsx` | `InvestmentContext.tsx` |
| components | `{ComponentName}.tsx` | `RateSelector.tsx` |

## Investment data keys

| Key | Description |
|-----|-------------|
| `combinedData` | Merged investment + pension rows per year |
| `pensionData` | Pension-only rows (Crelan + Baloise) |
| `monthlyTarget` | Monthly savings needed to stay on track |
| `rate` | Current investment return rate (5, 7, or 10%) |
